dc_title_s: Glen V. Mills directory maps of Ann Arbor, Ypsilanti, and Washtenaw County 1894
dc_description_s: 1 atlas (4 pages) ; 36 x 32 cm|Glen V. Mills published a directories for towns and cities across Michigan in the 1890s and early 1900s. Presumably these maps would serve as an accompaniment to the directories.|Includes full page maps of Ann Arbor, Ypsilanti, and Washtenaw county. Smaller maps of surrounding cities are included on the last page of the atlas.|The maps of the cities include streets names and railroad lines. The Washtenaw county map shows plats and city and town boundaries.
